#Text=This photo , taken by Ansel Adams at Grand Teton National Park in
#Text=Wyoming , was provided by the National Archives as part of its partnership with WikipediaImage : Ansel Adams .
#Text=( ( WN ) ) Having worked in the National Archives for a few weeks now , has your approach to or perception of your work in Wikipedia or the National Archives changed in any way ?
#Text=( ( DMP ) ) I really was n't sure what to expect when I got here .
#Text=The staff have all been exceedingly welcoming and cooperative which is a major relief .
#Text=The real work has been figuring out what I can do and where best to spend my time .
#Text=Most of the National Archives ' documents are not digitized , and possibly not even cataloged on the item-level .
#Text=Those certainly include some items that Wikimedians would like to use for their projects , but it remains to be seen how much I can realistically do in one summer with those documents .

#Text=I do want to get as much digital content as possible on Commons , but aside from the technological challenges we face at Commons in trying to figure out how to do mass uploads , the situation with the National Archives ' scan files is just as much of a barrier .
#Text=They are often confusingly named , difficult to locate , or incomplete .
#Text=I hit the ground running with the upload of an important batch of Ansel Adams photographs , but it turns out that that was actually the lowest-possible hanging fruit .
#Text=( ( WN ) ) What challenges do you foresee having to face in your work ?
#Text=( ( DMP ) )
#Text=The real challenges are about organization , both of documents — as I mentioned — and of people .
#Text=One of the biggest challenges is that we need Wikimedians to get on board with the project in a big way .
#Text=This is an incredible opportunity for us as a project , but it requires a special community effort to take full advantage of it .

#Text=We need volunteers to tag articles , to categorize media , to help with templates and coding tools , to write related article content , to transcribe and proofread texts , to add new images to articles , to digitally restore images , and so on .
#Text=I can personally serve as the point of contact between the National Archives and Wikimedia , but it needs to be much more than that to be a successful project .

#Text=At this point , the project spaces I am creating on-wiki are my attempt to create an inviting and useful infrastructure to serve as a hub for this effort , but they are not organically grown like most Wikimedia projects .
#Text=I , and various helpers with templates and coding , have magicked them into existence in the last few weeks .
#Text=They need participants to sign up and adopt them as their own so we can really get the ball rolling .
